peregrine.worker.clientd.requests
Interface RequestSizeable

All Known Subinterfaces:
BackendRequestFactory
All Known Implementing Classes:
BackendRequest, GetBackendRequest, GetBackendRequestFactory, ScanBackendRequest, ScanBackendRequestFactory
public interface RequestSizeable

Used so that we can estimate the size of a request before we add an item to the queue. I'm aware that "sizeable" is not a word and the real english word is "sizable" but we're exposing the "size()" method so I think it makes sense to call this "sizeable".

Method Summary
 int size()
          Return the number of items this request represents.
 

Method Detail

size

int size()
Return the number of items this request represents. For some requests this is an approximate size. SCAN for example doesn't know ahead of time how many entries it will match (it may be none).
